Package: ALLSPICER
Type: Package
Title: Tool for ALLelic Spectrum of Pleiotropy Informed Correlated Effects
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Wenhan Lu
Maintainer: Wenhan Lu <wlu@broadinstitute.org>
Description: A likelihood statistical test to identify allelic heterogeneity within a pleiotropic gene, defined as an imperfect correlation between the effects of variants within that gene on the two traits.It uses summary statistics from single-variant association tests and accounts for the phenotypic correlation. 
